# SEO Guidelines

## Per-Page SEO (Required)

Every page must call `usePageSEO`:

```jsx
usePageSEO({
  title: t(translations.seo.someTitle),
  description: t(translations.seo.someDescription)
})
```

This hook updates `document.title`, meta description, OG tags, Twitter cards, `og:url`, and canonical link.

All SEO strings live in `translations.seo` in `src/translations/index.js`. For new pages, add both `Title` and `Description` entries for EN/BG.

## Baseline Metadata

`index.html` provides defaults for: title, description, OG tags, Twitter cards, canonical, hreflang, and JSON-LD.

## Structured Data

JSON-LD in `index.html` includes:
- HairSalon entity with address, phone, hours
- `aggregateRating` (5.0 stars, 57 reviews)
- Service catalog with EUR prices
- `sameAs` links to Instagram and Studio24

When updating services, hours, or rating -- update the JSON-LD too.

## Google Reviews

- Hardcoded reviews in `src/data/reviews.js`
- `RatingBadge` component shows the 5.0 rating
- `ReviewsCarousel` rotates through reviews
- Update `reviews.js` and `aggregateRating` in JSON-LD when new reviews come in

## On-Page Checklist

- Unique title + description via `usePageSEO`
- Semantic headings (one `<h1>` per page)
- Meaningful `alt` text on images
- Internal links via `<Link>` from react-router-dom
- `loading="lazy"` on non-critical images
- Stable layout (reserve space for hero/sliders)

## Static SEO Files

- `public/robots.txt` with sitemap reference
- `public/sitemap.xml` listing all routes
